.SH NAME
polyglot\-task\-contract \- the validated workflow contract
.SH PURPOSE
This page defines the standard task workflow used by the repository and
its starters.
.SH WHEN TO USE
Read this page whenever you need to know the supported commands or the
completion bar.
.SH PRIMARY COMMANDS
.IP
.EX
task init
task lint
task test
task scan
task ci
.EE
.PP
Optional helpers may also exist:
.IP
.EX
task format
task test:fast
task test:unit
task test:integration
task test:acceptance
task test:property
task deps:inventory
task deps:plan
task deps:report
task upgrade
.EE
.SH WORKFLOW
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]task init\f[R] Bootstrap the local environment.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]task lint\f[R] Run code quality and type checks.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]task test\f[R] Run automated tests.
.IP \(bu 2
Focused \f[CR]task test:*\f[R] helpers may exist for fast, unit,
integration, acceptance, or property suites.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]task scan\f[R] Run security checks and write artifacts.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]task ci\f[R] Run the full validated workflow.
.SH OUTPUTS / ARTIFACTS
The main artifact convention is:
.IP
.EX
\&.artifacts/scans/
.EE
.PP
Dependency\-maintenance paths may also write:
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]dependency\-inventory.json\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]dependency\-plan.json\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]dependency\-report.json\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]dependency\-report.md\f[R]
.SH COMMON FAILURES
.IP \(bu 2
Declaring work complete after \f[CR]lint\f[R] or \f[CR]test\f[R] without
running \f[CR]scan\f[R].
.IP \(bu 2
Using helper tasks as a replacement for \f[CR]task ci\f[R].
.SH GUIDANCE
.IP \(bu 2
The safe default completion bar is \f[CR]task ci\f[R].
.IP \(bu 2
Use helper tasks to inspect or prepare changes, not to bypass
verification.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]task test\f[R] remains the full automated test bar when focused
\f[CR]task test:*\f[R] helpers are present.
.IP \(bu 2
Keep artifact locations stable and inspectable.
